terviewing skills.       Interviews     Interview Types         Interview Types   Employers use different types of interviews to vet job and/or internship candidates in today’s job market.  It is important that you understand why employers use each type of interview during your internship and/or job search.   Interview Types and Why Employers Use Each Type         Tips for video or phone interviews         Tips for video or phone interviews   Follow these tips if you are participating in a phone or video interview:   Phone Interview Tips  Video Interview Tips         How can I practice interviewing?         How can I practice interviewing?   Students can strengthen their interview skills by signing up for a practice or “mock interview” with a UIC Career Advisor.  Following the practice interview, you will receive feedback about interviewing strengths and areas to improve.  Students can log into UICcareers.com to obtain access to the Mock Interview module in which students can tailor and record responses to common interview questions.  Recordings of interviews are then reviewed by a member of the Career Services team.   Mock Interview Instruction handout         What should I wear to an interview?         What should I wear to an interview?   It is important to dress appropriately for interviews because first impressions count.  The suggested dress code for interviews is business attire. If you are not sure what that means, read the document below for more information.   Tips on What to Wear to an Interview         Land the job through employer and industry research         Land The Job Through Employer And Industry Research   Another key component of interview success is doing research about the employer and industry to learn about current trends that you can speak about in your interview.  UIC Library offers FREE resources to UIC students to learn about employers and industries.   UIC Library Resources- Researching Employers         Things not to do in an interview         Things not to do in an interview              Key Resources for Preparation Before, During and After Your Interview     Believe it or not, even the most qualified job seekers need to prepare for job interviews. Why? Interviewing is a learned skill and there are no second chances to make a great first impression. Review these tips to enhance your interviewing skills.     Before Your Interview    Before Interview - Common Interview Questions   Behavioral Interview Questions      During Your Interview    During Interview - List of Questions to Ask      After Your Interview    After Interview - Sample Thank You Notes/Emails           Schedule an advising appointment          Students    Back to main content           Career Programs and Events    Career Advising    Career Exploration     Career Education Resources      Resumes, CVs, and Cover Letters    Interviews    Jobs    Internships    Networking    Student Success Stories     Graduate Outcomes    Journey to Success Nomination Form                    UIC Logo        Career Services         Students    Career Planning Guide    Make an Appointment    FAQs      Employers    Post a Position    UICcareers.com      Campus Partners    Campus Partners    Program/Workshop Request Forms        Footer Menu    Career Programs and Events    UICcareers    UIC Student Employment Office         Contact   Suite 3050 1200 West Harrison Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-2300  Fax: (312) 413-0383  careerservices@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Twitter    YouTube             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 